dict.string: {\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1187\cocoasubrtf370 \cocoascreenfonts1{\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;\f1\fnil\fcharset0 LucidaGrande;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} {\*\listtable{\list\listtemplateid1\listhybrid{\listlevel\levelnfc23\levelnfcn23\leveljc0\leveljcn0\levelfollow0\levelstartat1\levelspace360\levelindent0{\*\levelmarker \{square\}}{\leveltext\leveltemplateid1\'01\uc0\u9642 ;}{\levelnumbers;}\fi-360\li720\lin720 }{\listname ;}\listid1}} {\*\listoverridetable{\listoverride\listid1\listoverridecount0\ls1}} \pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural \ls1\ilvl0 \f0\fs48 \cf0 {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }A generalization of subroutines\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 } \i AKA green threads, co-expressions, fibers, generators \i0 \ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Some may remember the old windows event loop\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Behavior similar to that of subroutines \ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Coroutines can call other coroutines\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Execution may but may not later return to the point of invocation\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Often demonstrated on Producer/Consumer scenario}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1187\cocoasubrtf370 \cocoascreenfonts1{\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;\f1\fnil\fcharset0 LucidaGrande;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} {\*\listtable{\list\listtemplateid1\listhybrid{\listlevel\levelnfc23\levelnfcn23\leveljc0\leveljcn0\levelfollow0\levelstartat1\levelspace360\levelindent0{\*\levelmarker \{square\}}{\leveltext\leveltemplateid1\'01\uc0\u9642 ;}{\levelnumbers;}\fi-360\li720\lin720 }{\listname ;}\listid1}} {\*\listoverridetable{\listoverride\listid1\listoverridecount0\ls1}} \pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural \ls1\ilvl0 \f0\fs48 \cf0 {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Buffers, phases (BufferedJoinedIterator)\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Emulations by threads (PipeJoinedIterator)\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Byte-code manipulation (CoJoinedIterator)\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }A need for JVM support, some future JSR?\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }For some implementations see the references\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }In this presentation I use Continuations library developed by Matthias Mann (http://www.matthiasmann.de/content/view/24/26/)\ }

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1187\cocoasubrtf370 \cocoascreenfonts1{\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;\f1\fnil\fcharset0 LucidaGrande;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} {\*\listtable{\list\listtemplateid1\listhybrid{\listlevel\levelnfc23\levelnfcn23\leveljc0\leveljcn0\levelfollow0\levelstartat1\levelspace360\levelindent0{\*\levelmarker \{square\}}{\leveltext\leveltemplateid1\'01\uc0\u9642 ;}{\levelnumbers;}\fi-360\li720\lin720 }{\listname ;}\listid1}} {\*\listoverridetable{\listoverride\listid1\listoverridecount0\ls1}} \pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural \ls1\ilvl0 \f0\fs48 \cf0 {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Iterators\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Producer/Consumer chains\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }State machines\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Visitors with loops instead of callbacks\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Pull parsers\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Loggers\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Observers, listeners, notifications\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Generally capable of converting PUSH algorithms to PULL\ }

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1187\cocoasubrtf370 \cocoascreenfonts1{\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;\f1\fnil\fcharset0 LucidaGrande;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} {\*\listtable{\list\listtemplateid1\listhybrid{\listlevel\levelnfc23\levelnfcn23\leveljc0\leveljcn0\levelfollow0\levelstartat1\levelspace360\levelindent0{\*\levelmarker \{square\}}{\leveltext\leveltemplateid1\'01\uc0\u9642 ;}{\levelnumbers;}\fi-360\li720\lin720 }{\listname ;}\listid1}} {\*\listoverridetable{\listoverride\listid1\listoverridecount0\ls1}} \pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural \ls1\ilvl0 \f0\fs48 \cf0 {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }PULL, batch processing, offline\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Two-phase computational mode: Map and Reduce\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Map - filters, cleans or parses the input records\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Reduce - aggregates the records obtained from Map\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Easily distributable \ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Inspired by functional programming\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Benefits - scalable, thread-safe (no race conditions), simple computational model\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Rich libraries of algorithms - e.g. machine learning (Mahout)}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1187\cocoasubrtf370 \cocoascreenfonts1{\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;\f1\fnil\fcharset0 LucidaGrande;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} {\*\listtable{\list\listtemplateid1\listhybrid{\listlevel\levelnfc23\levelnfcn23\leveljc0\leveljcn0\levelfollow0\levelstartat1\levelspace360\levelindent0{\*\levelmarker \{square\}}{\leveltext\leveltemplateid1\'01\uc0\u9642 ;}{\levelnumbers;}\fi-360\li720\lin720 }{\listname ;}\listid1}} {\*\listoverridetable{\listoverride\listid1\listoverridecount0\ls1}} \pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural \ls1\ilvl0 \f0\fs48 \cf0 {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Could we write the same code for data streams?\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }We could keep thinking in MR paradigm \ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Perhaps, it would inherit the nice MR properties\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Sadly, streaming algorithms are inherently PUSH,\ incremental or event-driven, i.e. callbacks instead of loops\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }WordCount MR solution has 2 simple loops\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }It is a typical Producer/Consumer problem\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Coroutines should help us!\ \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural \cf0 \ }

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1187\cocoasubrtf370 \cocoascreenfonts1{\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;\f1\fnil\fcharset0 LucidaGrande;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} {\*\listtable{\list\listtemplateid1\listhybrid{\listlevel\levelnfc23\levelnfcn23\leveljc0\leveljcn0\levelfollow0\levelstartat1\levelspace360\levelindent0{\*\levelmarker \{square\}}{\leveltext\leveltemplateid1\'01\uc0\u9642 ;}{\levelnumbers;}\fi-360\li720\lin720 }{\listname ;}\listid1}} {\*\listoverridetable{\listoverride\listid1\listoverridecount0\ls1}} \pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural \ls1\ilvl0 \f0\fs48 \cf0 {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Adoption of MR paradigm to data stream processing\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Built on top of coroutines (Producer/Consumer)\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Goes further than the original MR concepts\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Easy for anyone familiar with Hadoop (or other) \ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Open-sourced recently by AVAST\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }The core is practically production-ready (RC)\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }A lot of work to be done (networking, RPC)\ }

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf1187\cocoasubrtf370 \cocoascreenfonts1{\fonttbl\f0\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;\f1\fnil\fcharset0 LucidaGrande;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} {\*\listtable{\list\listtemplateid1\listhybrid{\listlevel\levelnfc23\levelnfcn23\leveljc0\leveljcn0\levelfollow0\levelstartat1\levelspace360\levelindent0{\*\levelmarker \{square\}}{\leveltext\leveltemplateid1\'01\uc0\u9642 ;}{\levelnumbers;}\fi-360\li720\lin720 }{\listname ;}\listid1}} {\*\listoverridetable{\listoverride\listid1\listoverridecount0\ls1}} \pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural \ls1\ilvl0 \f0\fs48 \cf0 {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Distributed stream processing easier\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Some techniques known from offline MR can be adopted more or less directly \ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Requires incremental algorithms and models\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }Many deployment options, flushing strategies\ {\listtext \f1 \uc0\u9642 \f0 }A lot of work to be done: communication protocol, machine learning and statistics algorithms, management tools, documentation ...}
